grep, awk, sed combo challenges

# grep
Use grep when you need:
✔ to find matching lines
✔ fast search
✔ pattern matching (regex)
✔ color-highlight matches
Syntax - grep [options] pattern [file...]
ex -  grep -i "error" file1.txt file2.log  (to search error in multiple files

# awk
Use awk when you need:
✔ Process column-based data
✔ Do calculations
✔ Convert or summarize data
✔ Print specific fields
✔ Work with CSV, logs, space-separated files
Syntax - awk options 'pattern {action}'
ex - awk '{print $4}' sample.txt
Terms used in awk
NR - No. of record/row
NF - No. of field
$0 - Print everithing
$1 , $2 - Field no.

# sed 
Use sed when you need:
✔ Search and replace
✔ Delete lines
✔ Insert or append lines
✔ Edit configuration files
✔ Remove characters / clean text

syntax - sed [options] 'script' [input_file(s)]
ex - sed 's/<string_to_change>/<new_string>/g' file_name  (How to replace a word in a file and show?)

